name: Omni-diff-use (ex. LucidMerge)
description:
I am satisfied with my first successful model mix, despite its slight instability. Given my previous lack of success, I consider it a victory. My goal was to achieve realism without going too far and maintaining a flexible model. My process involved using RealismEngine, AnalogMadness, and 526mix. I applied LifeLikeDiffusion after the FAD was subtracted from it. Since LifeLike already contains the Analog, I did not verify which version, and I made the weight of the new version smaller just in case. As far as I can tell, the model is behaving fairly neutrally. Of course, I will need to further explore its limitations, so please do not regard the model as something fully realized and thought out. These are just the first steps.

P.S.: Yeah...i forgot CineDiffusion.

I.S.S.: I've noticed that the number of followers is significantly lower than the number of downloads, which is understandable. However, it's surprising that there are people who appreciate my work but haven't followed me yet. I'm grateful for all those who appreciate my work, but I'd love to see more active engagement from our community. There will be more LoRA, text inversions, and I’ll be regularly updating and improving styles for my models. Plus, you’ll probably be able to peek at the working prompts. So join in the process - don’t forget about the importance of feedback.

Inpaint model works great with 'Poor man's outpainting' script, make sure you use the original prompt, settings and seed.

DDIM sampling is required in general inpaint mode (in case you didn't know).
